Using OpenWRT on Bifferboard. 
Bifferboard is permanently attached to weather station display

opkg update
opkg install bash vim

=======
BIFFBOOT CONFIG
===============
Configuration values:
bootsource:  on-board flash
console:     enabled
nic:         enabled
boottype:    Linux 2.6 parameter block
loadaddress: 0x00400000
cmndline:    rootfstype=squashfs,jffs2 console=uart,io,0x3f8 init=/etc/preinit ubi.mtd=rootfs <-- remove the console parameter if using homebuilt OpenWRT
kernelmax:   0x0010

BASIC SETUP
===========
If using the standard Biff image from http://sites.google.com/site/bifferboard/Home/factory-firmware then note the contents of http://sites.google.com/site/bifferboard/Home/howto/install-opkg-files
Edit /etc/opkg.conf and change the URL in the first line to http://downloads.openwrt.org/kamikaze/8.09/rdc/packages/

WIRELESS
========
Using Ralink RT2870 USB device

opkg update
opkg install usbutils
opkg install kmod-rt2800-usb

TIME
====
Bifferboard has no RTC, so an external time source is vital

opkg update
opkg install luci-app-ntpc

NETWORKING
==========
opkg update
opkg install luci-app-openvpn

GETTING DATA
============
Install fowsr on the Bifferboard, and periodically upload to server for processing
opkg update
opkg install fowsr
